<paragraph id="FE532066475D9726D9D12033893EAC87" pageId="0" pageNumber="56883">
The species (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="8751F88E1134D45C80A31EBEEF66488D" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F5979094" captionText="Figure 6. Selected habitus illustrations of Gerromorpha of Mindoro A. Hebrus sp.; B. Mesovelia vittigera; C. Hydrometra mindoroensis; D. Microvelia douglasi; E. Pseudovelia cf. curvata; F. Strongylovelia mindoroensis; G. Rhagovelia mindoroensis; H. Rhagovelia raddai. Scale bars 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.8.e56883.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/467166" pageId="0" pageNumber="56883">6</figureCitation>
B) is widely distributed in the tropics and subtropics of the Old World, including the Philippines (
<bibRefCitation id="8CC070AF265195E458EE438ACEC83804" author="Zettel, H." journalOrPublisher="Zeitschrift der Arbeitsgemeinschaft Oesterreichischer Entomologen" pageId="0" pageNumber="56883" pagination="85 - 140" refId="B5979710" refString="Zettel, H., 2014. Annotated catalogue of semi-aquatic bugs (Hemiptera: Heteroptera: Gerromorpha) of Luzon Island, the Philippines, with descriptions of new species. Zeitschrift der Arbeitsgemeinschaft Oesterreichischer Entomologen 66: 85 - 140" title="Annotated catalogue of semi-aquatic bugs (Hemiptera: Heteroptera: Gerromorpha) of Luzon Island, the Philippines, with descriptions of new species" volume="66" year="2014">Zettel 2014</bibRefCitation>
). See Fig. 
<figureCitation id="C024F801E807DBD35ED7C7D1C0CC6122" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F5979098" captionText="Figure 7. Distribution of the collecting sites of Gerromorpha material (part 1) treated in this study." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.8.e56883.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/467247" pageId="0" pageNumber="56883">7</figureCitation>
for additional records.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4C620D320FA0FE88A93ECF461C3FB12C" pageId="0" pageNumber="56883" type="taxon discussion">
<paragraph id="8A39C9EB0C4A1A9751134A62A0BDE266" pageId="0" pageNumber="56883">Taxon discussion</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EAA520ABC1DCBD8EA64E0E32CB2C125E" pageId="0" pageNumber="56883">
For identification, refer to the key by 
<bibRefCitation id="61C1B911F25954D9D45366629933435B" author="Yang, C. M." journalOrPublisher="The Raffles Bulletin of Zoology" pageId="0" pageNumber="56883" pagination="53 - 60" refId="B5979633" refString="Yang, C. M., Murphy, D., 2011. Guide to the Aquatic Heteroptera of Singapore and Peninsular Malaysia. 6. Mesoveliidae, with description of a new species from Singapore. The Raffles Bulletin of Zoology 59 (1): 53 - 60" title="Guide to the Aquatic Heteroptera of Singapore and Peninsular Malaysia. 6. Mesoveliidae, with description of a new species from Singapore" volume="59" year="2011">Yang and Murphy (2011)</bibRefCitation>
. All specimens examined were apterous.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="9CFFF217365A0D2BDB9D75A38003A519" pageId="0" pageNumber="56883" type="habitat">
<paragraph id="17BB54CD0AAC6636D2F56FA3E0E52A1D" pageId="0" pageNumber="56883">Habitat</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B18CAD9723E0BBABB698173454518048" pageId="0" pageNumber="56883">
<taxonomicName id="C4736CC5BDB100636590554E1F876A5E" class="Insecta" family="Mesoveliidae" genus="Mesovelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Mesovelia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="56883" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C1D51507EA9569B3A80DF259BAA2FC79" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="56883">Mesovelia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species are commonly found amongst marginal vegetation in standing waters of ponds and streams. 
<taxonomicName id="E9B7400C464E68FA754B036B63292256" authorityName="Horvath" authorityYear="1895" class="Insecta" family="Mesoveliidae" genus="Mesovelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Mesovelia vittigera" order="Hemiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="56883" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vittigera">
<emphasis id="530B43838FFCAC30ACC0EF50CF6DBC48" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="56883">Mesovelia vittigera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken id="D65B5D20492A42E0C395D6B1BBD64E48" originalValue="Horváth">Horvath</normalizedToken>
, 1895 (see 
<bibRefCitation id="49DF3E7D0BBFC85D42489C724C475711" author="Horvath, G." journalOrPublisher="Revue d'Entomologie" pageId="0" pageNumber="56883" pagination="152 - 165" refId="B5982080" refString="Horvath, G., 1895. Hemipteres nouveaux d'Europe et des pays limitrophes. Revue d'Entomologie 14: 152 - 165" title="Hemipteres nouveaux d'Europe et des pays limitrophes" volume="14" year="1895">
<normalizedToken id="364AD1DA3E53F92B694C4114DDE00865" originalValue="Horváth">Horvath</normalizedToken>
1895
</bibRefCitation>
) can also be found in brackish-water habitats (
<bibRefCitation id="10B4045951EC5528C2F04B372DD37A7A" author="Yang, C. M." journalOrPublisher="The Raffles Bulletin of Zoology" pageId="0" pageNumber="56883" pagination="53 - 60" refId="B5979633" refString="Yang, C. M., Murphy, D., 2011. Guide to the Aquatic Heteroptera of Singapore and Peninsular Malaysia. 6. Mesoveliidae, with description of a new species from Singapore. The Raffles Bulletin of Zoology 59 (1): 53 - 60" title="Guide to the Aquatic Heteroptera of Singapore and Peninsular Malaysia. 6. Mesoveliidae, with description of a new species from Singapore" volume="59" year="2011">Yang and Murphy 2011</bibRefCitation>
). We found several specimens on shaded, wet rocks and at the stream littoral with mineral substrates (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="93CF435639AA54EA6BC89CB8EF7A3833" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F5978773" captionText="Figure 1. Sampling sites at northern Mindoro (Baco, Puerto Galera). A. the first author sampling at site 396; B. Tagbinai Malaki River (305); C. Tukunan River at &quot; Hidden Paradise &quot; (303); D. lower Dulangan River (356)." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.8.e56883.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/434061" pageId="0" pageNumber="56883">1</figureCitation>
B).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
